    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle, cut your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into slices (4 per person!) and add to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, transfer to the oven for 8 min or toasted, then add to a plate and reserve the tray</p><p>Finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garlic</strong>, then add to an<strong> oven-proof dish </strong>with your <strong>chicken stock mix, </strong>1/3 of your <strong>parsley & tarragon pesto</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir together </p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>breast joint[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then coat the chicken in the <strong>remaining parsley & tarragon pesto</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>seasoned chicken </strong>to the pan, skin-side down and cook for 2-3 min on each side, or until golden and reserve the pan</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is golden, transfer it to the <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (skin side up) and cover the dish in <strong>tin foil</strong>, then put the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min</p><p>While the chicken is cooking, cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into small bite-sized cubes and line the reserved baking tray (or two!) with <strong>baking paper</strong> and add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for 25 min or until crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>parmentier potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Zest<strong> half </strong>your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Roll the <strong>zested lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once the chicken has had an initial 20 min, remove it from the oven and discard the tin foil, then add your <strong>clotted cream</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>to the dish and give everything a good mix up, season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and return the dish to the oven for a final 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through and crispy (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy tarragon chicken</strong></p><p>Once ready, transfer the <strong>roast chicken </strong>to a clean board to rest for 2-3 min and give your sauce a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high</p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed green beans </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and cook, lid on for 8-10 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a medium heatproof bowl with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and put it in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 1 min or until melted, once melted, whisk through your <strong>mayo </strong>with a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong> and the <strong>grated garlic</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli lime butter mayo</strong></p><p>Toss the <strong>cooked prawns </strong>through the <strong>chilli lime butter mayo</strong> \u2013 these are your <strong>chilli lime butter prawns</strong>, top the <strong>ciabatta crostinis</strong> with the <strong>chilli lime butter prawns </strong>and garnish with the<strong> lime zest \u2013 </strong>these are your<strong> chilli lime butter prawn crostinis</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-lime-butter-prawn-crostini-creamy-tarragon-chicken-and-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To start, serve the <strong>chilli lime butter prawn crostinis</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>rested</strong> <strong>chicken</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> sliced chicken </strong>over the<strong> creamy tarragon sauce </strong>with the <strong>thyme parmentier potatoes </strong>and<strong> cooked green beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
